mysterious /mɪˈstɪərɪəs/

1. ADJ Someone or something that is mysterious is strange and is not known about or understood. 神秘的; 难以理解的 

例： He died in mysterious circumstances. 他死得蹊跷。 

例： A mysterious illness confined him to bed for over a month. 一种怪病让他卧床一个多月。 

2. mysteriously ADV 神秘地 

例： A couple of messages had mysteriously disappeared. 几条信息已经神秘地消失了。 

3. ADJ If someone is mysterious about something, they deliberately do not talk much about it, sometimes because they want to make people more interested in it. 诡秘的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： As for his job – well, he was very mysterious about it. 至于他的工作–嘿，他对此十分诡秘。 

4. mysteriously ADV 诡秘地 [ADV after v] 

例： Asked what she meant, she said mysteriously: 'Work it out for yourself.' 当被问及她什么意思时，她诡秘地说：“你自己想想吧。”

